quran[58]{c,v,t}:
  37,145,But We cast him up on the naked shore in a state of sickness
  37,146,And We caused to grow over him a spreading plant of the gourd kind
  37,147,And We sent him to a hundred thousand people or more
  37,148,And they believed. So We permitted them to enjoy their time
  37,149,"Then ask them, do the females belong to God and the males to you"
  37,150,Or did you see Us create the angels female
  37,151,Is it not that they say falsely
  37,152,“God has children”? But they are liars
  37,153,Did He choose daughters over sons
  37,154,What is the matter with you? How judge you
  37,155,Will you not then receive advice
  37,156,Or have you an authority manifest
  37,157,Then bring your book if you are truthful
  37,158,And they have created a blood relationship between Him and the jinn. But the jinn know that they have indeed to appear
  37,159,"Glory be to God, He is free from the things they ascribe to Him"
  37,160,"Not so the servants of God, sincere and devoted"
  37,161,Indeed neither you nor those you worship
  37,162,Can lead any into temptation concerning God
  37,163,Except those whom are themselves heading to the blazing fire
  37,164,"“Not us, only for him is a place known"
  37,165,“And indeed we are arranged in ranks
  37,166,“And we are indeed those who declare God's glory.”
  37,167,And there were those who said
  37,168,“If only we had before us a message from those in the past
  37,169,"“We would certainly have been servants of God, sincere.”"
  37,170,"So they reject it, but soon will they know"
  37,171,Our word has already been passed on before to Our servants sent by Us
  37,172,So that they would certainly be assisted
  37,173,And that Our forces surely must conquer
  37,174,So turn away from them for a little while
  37,175,"And watch them, and they soon will see"
  37,176,Do they wish to rush our punishment
  37,177,"But when it descends into the open space before them, terrible will be the morning for those who were warned"
  37,178,So turn away from them for a little while
  37,179,And watch and they soon will see
  37,180,"Glory to your Lord, the Lord of Honor and Power, free from what they ascribe to Him"
  37,181,And peace on the messengers
  37,182,"And praise God, the Guardian Evolver of all the worlds"
  38,1,"Saad. By the Quran, full of advice"
  38,2,But the unbelievers are steeped in self-glory and separatism
  38,3,"How many generations before them did We destroy? In the end they cried, when there was no longer time for being saved"
  38,4,"So they wonder how a warner has come to them from among themselves, and the unbelievers say, “This is a deceiver telling lies"
  38,5,“Has he made the gods all into one God? Truly this is a curious thing.”
  38,6,"And the leader among them walks away saying, “Walk away, and remain constant to your gods, for this is truly a thing created"
  38,7,“We never heard the likes of this among the people of these latter days. This is nothing but a fabrication.”
  38,8,"“What, has the message been sent to him, of all people?” But they are in doubt concerning My message. No, they have not yet tasted My punishment"
  38,9,"Or have they the treasures of the mercy of your Lord, the Exalted in Power, and the Grantor of bounties without measure"
  38,10,"Or have they control of the heavens and the earth and all between? If so, let them ascend by means to reach that end"
  38,11,Soldiers there will be defeated among the companies
  38,12,Before them the people rejected Noah and ‘Ad. And Pharaoh the lord of stakes
  38,13,"And Thamud, the people of Lot, and the Companions of the Wood, these were the confederates"
  38,14,"Not one of them failed to reject the messengers, so My punishment came justly and inevitably"
  38,15,"They must only wait for a single mighty blast, and there will be no delay"
  38,16,"They say, “Our Lord, hasten to us our sentence before the Day of Account.”"
  38,17,"Have patience with what they say, and remember our servant David, the possessor of strength, for he constantly turned to God"
  38,18,"It was We Who made the hills declare in unison with him, Our praises in the evening and in the morning"
  38,19,"Then the birds gathered, and all turned with him to God"
  38,20,"We strengthened his kingdom, and gave him wisdom and sound judgment in speech and decision"